[The 10 countries that have been re-infected with wild poliovirus
related to the ongoing transmission in Nigeria are Benin, Botwana,
Burkina Faso, Cameroon, Chad, Cote d'Ivoire, Central African
Republic, Guinea, Mali, Sudan. As mentioned in earlier postings, the
ongoing polio transmission in Nigeria was a result of suspension of
vaccination activities in Kano State. One hopes that this issue has
now been resolved and with participation of Kano in the current
25-country vaccination campaign, interruption of transmission of the
wild poliovirus in Africa will be achieved. - Mod.MPP]
